## Overview

These five flows define how DealForge AI should behave when a user runs deal analysis. They span from the moment a user submits a deal prompt to the final formatted deliverable — covering tool calling, LLM resilience, output quality, and document retrieval.

The primary user interaction paths in DealForge are:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User submits deal prompt] --> B{Entry Path}
    B -->|Chat Pipeline| C[Clarify → Plan → Execute Tasks]
    B -->|Full Workflow| D[Create Deal → Run Workflow → Download Report]
    B -->|OFAS Mission| E[Create Mission → Monitor → Review Gates]
    B -->|Direct Agent| F[Run Single Agent]
    C --> G[Agent Execution Layer]
    D --> G
    E --> G
    F --> G
    G --> H[Tool-Backed Analysis]
    H --> I[Formatted Output]
```

All four paths converge on the same agent execution layer — meaning the fixes in these flows improve every interaction path simultaneously.

